Yet, when I run the following code in matlab
```A = rand(2000,2000);
B = rand(2000,2000);
v = rand(2000,1);
tic
D=zeros(size(A));
D = A;
for i =1:100
    D = A + B;
    (D)*v;
end
toc
tic
for i =1:100
    (A*v+B*v);
end
toc
```
The opposite is true. Av+Bv is over twice as fast. Any explanations?

